The paper deals with the analysis of the asymptotic growth of the number of overlap-free words, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also introduces new algorithms to compute spectral characteristics of sets of matrices, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also uses concepts from dynamical systems (cs.DS) and statistical inference (cs.SI) to estimate the growth rate of overlap-free words.
